data.title: Las Vegas NBA Summer League 2024: Complete roster of every team
data.meta_description: The NBA Summer League starts today from Las Vegas and before we sink our teeth in to the buffet of games, let's take a look at each team’s roster.
data.text:
The NBA 2K25 Summer League starts today and before the games get under way, we need to get familiar with each of the squads. There won’t be very many names you recognize on your favorite team’s roster, but we will get a first look at some of the most recognizable names of tomorrow over the next ten days.

Focus on the French

The Cleveland Cavaliers and the Orlando Magic open up the action in Las Vegas to kick off a full slate of basketball over the next week and a half. As you might have heard, there is no Victory Wembanyama or LeBron James or any other sort of generational talent as of yet in this draft, so the excitement level is not boiling over just yet in the City of Sin.

That being said there is plenty to look forward to in this year’s edition of the Summer League. While there is no Wemby, there are two Frenchmen that headlined the NBA Draft, going No. 1 and 2. Zaccharie Risacher and Alex Sarr are going to be ones to keep an eye.

Obviously we can’t talk about the NBA without mentioning Bronny James these days. Bronny and the Lakers will have their handful of games, and he will look to be a bit more efficient on the offensive end than he was in the California Classic when he scored a total of 7 points over two games.

There will be plenty of players to keep an eye, but just incase just need a little reference, here are all the players that will be participating in the Summer League.
